  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nThere currently isn't a mechanism to shutdown the client gracefully on a critical error. \r\n\r\nSpecifically in #1483, if a listener fails, we should check to see how many libp2p listeners exist. If there are none, then we should gracefully terminate the client. \r\n\r\nThis could like like sending a network message to the `network` thread which terminates the event loop. The global `executor` maybe could ensure that the network thread is a alive. If not, terminate the client gracefully. \r\n\r\nAlternatively build a shutdown mechanism (be it a oneshot or function) that is accessible to many of the ligthhouse sub-components. \r\n",
